TITLE: Searching with Fuse.js in a TypeScript Application
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet initializes Fuse.js with a sample dataset and specifies which object fields ('name', 'email') to search. The configuration uses options like minMatchCharLength and threshold for search performance and accuracy tuning. It demonstrates importing Fuse, setting up data and options, executing a search, and outputting the results, requiring the 'fuse.js' dependency installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/haydenbleasel/next-forge/blob/main/docs/addons/fuse.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import Fuse from 'fuse.js';

const data = [
  { id: 1, name: 'John Doe', email: 'john.doe@example.com' },
  { id: 2, name: 'Jane Doe', email: 'jane.doe@example.com' },
];

const fuse = new Fuse(data, {
  keys: ['name', 'email'],
  minMatchCharLength: 1,
  threshold: 0.3,
});

const results = fuse.search('john');

console.log(results);
```

